docs.text: jackie brown is a highly anticipated feature film from quentin tarantino , whose last film was the huge hit pulp fiction .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: after mediocre acting jobs , tarantino returns to what made his name a household one : directing and writing .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: jackie brown is the result , and it is fantastic entertainment .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: despite excellent direction from tarantino , the cast steals the film , giving one good performance after another .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: pam grier gives a stunning performance as jackie brown , and she is supported by an incredible mix of talent--samuel l . jackson , bridget fonda , michael keaton , robert de niro , and robert forster .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: more than likely , you will see a few of these names in the oscar pool come oscar nominations .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: describing a quentin tarantino film is very difficult , as you really can't say much or you spoil it for everyone else .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: i will tread lightly .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: jackie brown opens with an impressive shot of jackie brown ( grier ) in a blue outfit walking through the airport .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the camera tracks along with her , and ends up revealing her occupation .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: we are also introduced to ordell robbie ( jackson ) , who sells illegal guns to interested buyers . . .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: for a hefty price .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: ms . brown carries the money from buyer to ordell in order to keep the cops away .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: however , an fbi agent ( keaton ) and a local l . a . cop ( michael bowen ) are out to find ordell and catch him while taking the money .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: they try to reach him through beaumont livingston ( chris tucker ) , one of ordell's buyers , but he mysteriously ends up dead .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: they try again through brown , but she is hesitant to admit to any wrong-doing .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: but after unknowingly carrying some drugs for one of ordell's friends ( fonda ) , she is caught and sent to jail .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: ordell pays her bail through a bail bond agent , max cherry ( forster ) , and then wants to find out what she told the cops .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: after she claims to have said nothing , she reveals the fact that she will tell them about ordell in order to stay out of prison .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: ordell doesn't like this , but they both come up with a scheme to throw the feds and cops off their track .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: this scheme seems to be going as planned , but unexpected occurances may or may not foul up their goal .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: revealing more would spoil the fun of jackie brown , and that's the biggest reason to go see a tarantino film .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: tarantino seems to have a fascination with hitmen and unusual predicaments ( and slang terms ) , but they are always done very well and believably .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: his hitmen are normally cruel , but pleasant , in that nasty sort of way .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: they talk like normal people , except for when doing business , and they are rude to their girlfriends .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: of course , this is a tarantino film , and you know you can expect some awkward situations to arise .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: and perhaps the biggest flaw with jackie brown is the slow middle section in which the pace begins to drop .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: of course , tarantino fixes this by moving onto the climax of the film , adding a lot of his reservoir dogs-style storytelling to it .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: things are told from one person's perspective , and then from another , and then from another , each time learning more and more .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: this all leads up to a very interesting conclusion , which decides who is on whose side .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: on the technical side of jackie brown , quentin tarantino directs it with the same style as he did with his 1994 film .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: however , this time around it isn't as nearly as impressive or original .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the writing , on the other hand , is quite good , although i do find tarantino's use of slang terms offensive .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the story jumps back and forth in time as in pulp fiction , but it's much more easy to understand .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: his previous film needed a second viewing in order to understand the time differentiation , but jackie brown is very simply to follow , especially considering that the time is given during the " leaps " in time .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: perhaps this is a result of the screenplay being written from the novel " rum punch " by elmore leonard .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the dialogue is pretty much intelligent , and all the characters are fully realized .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the cinematography is very well done by guillermo navarro ( who has worked with tarantino on previous films ) and the editing is very good .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: and as with pulp fiction , the music is a highlight , bringing back memorable songs from the 70s and 80s .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the acting side of jackie brown is unforgettable .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the performances are incredibly rich , with hidden meaning behind every characters' actions .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: nothing is quite as it seems , and you can't really tell which side one person is on .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the real treat , of course , is pam grier who gives an astonishing performance as jackie brown .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: her poor living conditions are superceded by her superior wits , which play an important role in the film .

docs.text: watching grieg , i could tell what was going through her mind , even if i didn't know what she was thinking .

docs.text: her face portrays a lot of emotion that you can tell when she is sad , happy , or in deep thought .

docs.text: bridget fonda gives a very good performance as a druggie couch potato .

docs.text: michael keaton comes across very well , as does michael bowen .

docs.text: chris tucker has a small , but effective performance .

docs.text: but no matter . . .

docs.text: robert forster gives one of the best performances in the film , as he has one of the most developed characters .

docs.text: as a film by itself , jackie brown is a terrific piece of entertainment , with a complex plot to draw viewers in .

docs.text: however , one can not help but compare it to tarantino's pulp fiction , and expect great results .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: when compared , it comes up short , but not that short .
